    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's a lot easier said than done. counseling feels like just another task on a list that's already too long. everyone expects me to just pivot or find something new, but there's nothing else. i've spent my whole life building this one thing and it crumbled. it's just so much noise and pressure all the time. i honestly just feel like i'm drowning in it and i can't find the surface anymore.",
